comments.text:
You have to be epic level sneaky to do that with cowboy boots.  He just 
broke two guys neck with a slap, and a nose flick, and a third by pulling 
down on his beard, and then four dudes with a frisbee.  Despite how easily 
he dealt with the others, the main villain is always his equal, yup, this 
is late 80's to early 90's action movie at its finest.  Reminds me of a lot 
of Norris, Segal, and van Damme movies.

Hang on a second, he broke that guys neck with the back of his head.  This 
was like combining Segal action movies with the Chuck Norris meme.

Loved the ending.  It proved there really is such a thing as too much 
epicness for one person to have.﻿
